脚踝扭伤；踝关节扭伤；扭伤的脚踝
脚踝受伤；踝骨受伤；伤了脚踝
踝关节骨折；脚踝骨折；踝关节碎
占有优势的脚踝；突出的脚踝

bilingual.source: On the way, he hurt his ankle joint.
bilingual.target: 路上, 他伤了他的踝关节.

bilingual.source: The invention relates a bionic ankle joint.
bilingual.target: 一种仿生踝关节,属于机器人技术领域.

bilingual.source: He slipped on the stairs and put his ankle out.
bilingual.target: 他在楼梯上滑了一跤， 踝关节脱臼了。

bilingual.source: Ankle sprains accounted for about half of all injuries.
bilingual.target: 踝关节扭伤大约占所有受伤情况的一半.

bilingual.source: He stepped on a loose stone and twisted his ankle.
bilingual.target: 他踩在一块松动的石头上,把踝关节扭伤了.

bilingual.source: Intermittently there was swelling of arm, ankle and hands.
bilingual.target: 断断续续有肿胀的手臂，踝关节和手。

bilingual.source: Objective To discuss the therapy method of ankle joint fracture.
bilingual.target: 目的探讨正确处理踝关节骨折的治疗方法.

bilingual.source: ObjectiveTo measure cortical areas involved ankle dorsiflexion and planter flexion.
bilingual.target: 目的检测参与踝关节背屈和跖屈运动的脑区.

bilingual.source: The ankle bone articulates with the leg bones to form the ankle bones.
bilingual.target: 踝关节和腿骨相连,一起构成踝骨.

bilingual.source: The sprain of ankle could result in chronic instability without appropriate treatment.
bilingual.target: 踝关节扭伤处理不当常导致慢性踝关节不稳定.

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, my ankle. I can still hop to work.
yingyinNormal.zh: 噢，我的脚踝。我仍然可以单足跳着去工作。

yingyinNormal.en: So, Monica, how's the ankle? It's, well, why don't you tell them? After all it, is your ankle.
yingyinNormal.zh: 莫妮卡，脚踝如何？它啊，你何不告诉他们，这可是你的脚踝。

yingyinNormal.en: Miss rabbit has tripped over one of Richard's toys. Oh, my ankle. I can still hop to work.
yingyinNormal.zh: 兔小姐被理查德的一个玩具绊到了。哦，脚踝好疼，我还可以单脚跳去工作。

yingyinNormal.en: Before that, sewage and waste would just flow right down the street. Yeah, sometimes ankle deep.
yingyinNormal.zh: 之前污水跟废弃物会直接流到街上，有时到了脚踝。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh Pheebs, is that a new ankle bracelet? Wow. And you got a pedicure. Your feet are all dressed up.
yingyinNormal.zh: 菲比，那是新脚链吗？你去修过脚趾甲。你的脚打扮过。

yingyinNormal.en: Bye, sister. Miss rabbit has tripped over one of Richard's toys. Oh, my ankle. I can still hop to work.
yingyinNormal.zh: 一会见，妹妹。喔。兔小姐被理查德的一个玩具绊到了。哦，脚踝好疼，我还可以单脚跳去工作。

yingyinNormal.en: What are you waiting for? Oh, I can't swim because I sprain my ankle. And I think I might have a cough.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你们还在等什么呢？噢，我不能游泳，因为我的脚踝扭到了。我好像突然有点咳嗽了。

yingyinNormal.en: Hi. My friend here was taking down our Christmas lights and she fell off the balcony and may have broken her foot or ankle or something.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我朋友取、下圣诞灯时从阳台跌下来，可能伤了脚或者脚踝或者别的什么。

yingyinNormal.en: Not a waterproof shoe. That is relevant to the next part of my story. The ankle-deep puddle of warm apple juice. Apple juice? Maybe, maybe not.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这鞋不防水。这个细节和我接下来的故事大有关联。这个细节和我接下来的故事大有关联。那是一坑深及脚踝的"温热金黄苹果汁"。什么苹果汁？也许是，也许不是。
